(PROJECT SUMMARY) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(OBJECTIVE) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The goal of this project is to build a small reusable accelerator platform on the) Tj
T*
(PYNQ-Z2. The platform combines one register-mapped arithmetic block and one DMA-backed) Tj
T*
(streaming image block so the software and hardware sides can be tested together instead) Tj
T*
(of as separate demos.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The hardware side uses a Zynq processing system, AXI4-Lite for control, and AXI DMA for) Tj
T*
(the streaming image path. The multiplier is controlled through MMIO registers. The 3x3) Tj
T*
(filter receives one grayscale pixel per AXI stream beat and writes one output pixel per) Tj
T*
(beat back to memory through DMA.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(ARITHMETIC IP DESIGN) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The arithmetic block is a radix-4 Booth multiplier written in HLS. It accepts two) Tj
T*
(operands, a mode register, and returns a 64-bit product split across two 32-bit) Tj
T*
(registers. The mode field selects 8, 16, 24, or 32-bit operation and also selects signed) Tj
T*
(or unsigned arithmetic. The software driver writes the operands, sets the mode, starts) Tj
T*
(the block, waits for the done bit, and reads the result.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(STREAMING IMAGE IP DESIGN) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The image block is a streaming 3x3 filter with zero-padded borders. A small set of) Tj
T*
(runtime-selectable modes is included so the same block can be reused for pass-through,) Tj
T*
(blur, sharpen, Sobel X, Sobel Y, and Sobel magnitude. The HLS core keeps two line) Tj
T*
(buffers and one 3x3 window so the filter can run as a normal stream operator instead of) Tj
T*
(a frame buffer kernel.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(AXI INTEGRATION) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Both accelerators use AXI4-Lite for configuration. The image path also uses AXI4-Stream) Tj
T*
(and AXI DMA. The expected data path is PS DDR to DMA, DMA to filter IP, filter IP back) Tj
T*
(to DMA, and DMA back to PS DDR. The Vivado scripts in `hardware/vivado/scripts/` set up) Tj
T*
(the base project, the DMA block, the AXI control path, and the packaging step for the) Tj
T*
(overlay files.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(PYTHON CONTROL FLOW) Tj
T*
() Tj
ET
endstream
