() Tj
T*
(The Python side is split into small driver modules. `ArithmeticOverlay` handles register) Tj
T*
(writes and reads for the multiplier. `VisionOverlay` sets the image dimensions, writes) Tj
T*
(the filter mode, allocates buffers, launches DMA transfers, and returns the processed) Tj
T*
(frame. `AcceleratorOverlay` collects both blocks behind one object so the notebooks and) Tj
T*
(tests can use a shared control style.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(VERIFICATION) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The multiplier is checked with directed tests and random tests across several active) Tj
T*
(widths. The vision block is checked against a NumPy reference model for pass-through,) Tj
T*
(blur, sharpen, and Sobel modes. A mock MMIO and DMA backend is included so the whole) Tj
T*
(Python path can run on a host machine without a board.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(BENCHMARK RESULTS) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The sample benchmark JSON in `data/benchmark_results/sample_results.json` is generated) Tj
T*
(with the mock backend. It is only meant to check the control flow and report formatting.) Tj
T*
(On real hardware the multiplier should be measured against the ARM software path and the) Tj
T*
(filter should be measured in frame time and FPS with DMA included in the timing.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(LIMITATIONS) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(  - The repo does not include a checked-in bitstream because that is a build output.) Tj
T*
(  - The current image path uses grayscale frames to keep the stream kernel and tests) Tj
T*
(simple.) Tj
T*
(  - Real board-side benchmark numbers still need to be collected after Vivado and HLS) Tj
T*
(builds are complete.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(FUTURE WORK) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(  - add a MAC or FIR block to the arithmetic side) Tj
T*
(  - add tiled image support for larger frames) Tj
T*
(  - add a live HDMI or camera demo path) Tj
